Network Security Toolkit
This Python script provides essential network security tools:

Ping Test: Checks connectivity to a specified IP address.
Port Scanner: Identifies open TCP ports on a target IP.
Brute Force Password Cracker: Attempts to crack passwords using brute force.
Features:
Ping Test: Verify connectivity.
Port Scanner: Identify open ports.
Brute Force Password Cracker: Crack passwords.
Usage:
Input the target IP address.
Perform a ping test.
Specify port range to scan.
Scan for open TCP ports.
Input password for brute force attack.tells you how many tries a bruteforce tool like jacktheripper would attempt.
Dependencies:
Python 3.x
socket, itertools, string, os modules
Note: Use responsibly and with appropriate permissions.

GitHub: Network-Security-Toolkit
